author: @delightedhoney3747
text:
one of the things i love about svt is when they perform (or like dance, choreographed, sing) it is sooo much fun. it makes you feel like you wanna have fun with them too, and you will really know that they enjoy what they are doing, they love what they are doing. and they aren't doing it just for the sake of having a "work" to put out in the world. it's their job, alright, but the way they do it doesn't feel like it. it doesn't feel like work, it feels more like a passion. and i love how that passion reflects in what they do, what they show us. and you really know that these guys aren't here for fun or to be able to outstand others. they are here because this is their calling.

i hope that in the coming years they stay in the kpop industry, they won't lose that passion. i hope they continue to love what they are doing, and that love to not be burned out by how a little bit dark, negative and toxic the industry. i hope they won't get tired of doing music and showing it to the world. because you know the downside of making your passion as your professional job? is that when it gets too tough and too much pressure to get you on constant work, the love for that passion slowly disappears. it became like a mandatory thing you do just so you can survive. and you will start to hate the thing you once gave all your effort, time, love and your whole life. (ok i know i'm saying this from my own experience lol) and i hope svt won't ever feel that and they won't come to that point where giving up is the best solution they could think of. all the love, sebong! i'm busy but i will always and will continue supporting you from behind! ily13x!!

author: @che-che-che-checherrybomb6051
text:
Even I'm not a Carat back then, I always think that SVT is the most ideal boygroup ever! I mean, ofc all of kpop group are all talented af and that's a fact no one can deny, they all can sing and dance, but performance wise, I think SVT is just on a whole different level. For me, eventho I wasn't a Carats untill their last comeback, I always enjoy their performance. I love how they're seems so confident and relax on stage, like they always do this 'shouts' and having fun on stage, they are so good on lifting up audiens's mood! It's SOOOOOO good to watch their perfomance because they seems like enjoy the stage so much. I mean you can have a good performance but it's kinda hard to have a good and entertaining performance at once. And SVT do both easily! 
For other fandom, SVT also known as the group that never release a bad song and one of the best dance group in K-pop industry! When their song played on a Korean festival in my town everyone will sing it together. ALL of them, even if you're not a Carat you'll sing SVT's song. And the fact they also produce their own music and make their own choreography is just ğŸ‘ŒğŸ‘ŒğŸ‘ŒğŸ‘Œ
And their fans! Oh wow, how I respect Carats so much for being one of the most untoxic fandom ever and they also so fun! I always respect both SVT and their fans so much even before I join this fandom. And now, I'm a baby Carats! :'D eventho I feel a bit ashamed for join this fandom way too late, I always watch them since their debut era and can't help but slowly loving for their charm!
